FT  10 MAR 92 / UK Company News: High-Point runs up Pounds 64,000 loss
High-Point, the architect, surveyor and consulting engineer, incurred a
pre-tax loss of Pounds 64,000 for the six months to end-November compared
with a profit of Pounds 881,000.
The interim dividend is cut from 2.55p to 1.3p.
A further deterioration in the company's business climate, particularly the
construction industry, trimmed turnover from Pounds 29.35m to Pounds 28.2m.
First-half losses per share were 1.04p (earnings 11.19p)
